SIMPLE: sea_trout
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea trout
<hw>Sea" trout`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Any one of several species of true trouts which descend rivers and
enter the sea after spawning, as the European bull trout and salmon
trout, and the eastern American spotted trout.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The common squeteague, and the spotted squeteague.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>A California fish of the family <fam>Chiridae</fam>,
especially <spn>Hexagrammus decagrammus</spn>; -- called also
<altname>spotted rock trout</altname>. See <cref>Rock trout</cref>,
under <er>Rock</er>.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>A California sciaenoid fish
(<spn>Cynoscion nobilis</spn>); -- called also <altname>white sea
bass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea trumpet</ent>⟦br⟧
